By Moronke Boboye Phone Ikeja, – A 29-year-old man, Chibuike Ignatus, on Friday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing a Samsung A73 smart phone, valued N480,000. The defendant, who resides at 2, Obasa St., Anifowose, Ikeja, is charged with stealing. The prosecutor, Insp Glory Goodday, told the court that the offence was committed on Dec. 2 at Jumia Logistics Company, Ikeja. Goodday alleged that the installed Closed Circuit Television (CCTV) showed the defendant, who works with Jumia, stealing the Samsung smart phone. The offence, according to the prosecutor, contravenes section 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. The Magistrate, Mr O. O Odufuye, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N50,000 with one surety in like sum. Odufuye adjourned the case until Feb. 13, for mention.(NAN)( By Moronke BoboyeIkeja, - A 42-year-old unemployed man, Samson Ajayi,  on Wednesday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing from a hotel. The defendant, who resides at 10, Oluwole St., Shogunle, Mushin, Lagos State, is facing a count charge of  stealing. He, however, pleaded not guilty. According to… In "Metro" By MORONKE BOBOYE IKEJA- A 44-year-old woman, Anerobi Obianuju, was on Tuesday  docked in an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly beating up an official of the Power Holding Company of Nigeria(PHCN) while performing his duty. The defendant, a trader who resides at 7, Adesola Akande St., College road, Ogba, Lagos,… In "News" By Itohan Abara-Laserian Ikeja - A 34-year-old man, Adamu Yakubu, on Tuesday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing diesel worth N700,860. Yakubu, whose residential address was not provided, is facing a two-count charge bordering on stealing. He, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. The prosecutor, Mr… In "Metro"